“Let’s connect for a moment,” she said, pulling me into her intense eye contact.
We maintained eye contact longer than, I imagined, most would consider comfortable.
We “greeted” each other relying purely on eye contact.
In the 1990s, psychologist Arthur Aron conducted a study wherein he succeeded in getting a couple of strangers to fall in love using sustained eye contact.
Until then, Authentic Relating must rely on participant testimonials and passionate novitiates to enlarge their cultural impact—one relationship at a time.